=== POTS Subtypes: Neuropathic, Hyperadrenergic, Hypovolemic
  <sec:pots-cascade>

*Certainty: 0.55.* POTS subtypes are clinically validated in general POTS populations with standing/supine norepinephrine levels, autonomic testing, and treatment response patterns. Application to ME/CFS-POTS overlap supported by autonomic testing data showing high POTS prevalence (30--90% depending on cohort and definition). Subtype identification is not academic — the treatment for neuropathic POTS (midodrine) worsens hyperadrenergic POTS, and the treatment for hyperadrenergic POTS (beta-blockers) worsens neuropathic POTS. The wrong subtype treatment can make the patient worse. Subtype diagnosis through pharmacology is therefore clinically urgent.

